# harness secrets + config — copy to .env and fill in what you need (never commit .env).
# Every key is independently optional; a lane only needs its own keys (and many `hn travel`
# senses — weather/air/quakes/geocoding — are keyless and need nothing).

# ── travel (hn travel) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SerpAPI — flights + hotels (Google Flights / Google Hotels engines). Free 250 searches/mo.
# https://serpapi.com/manage-api-key
SERPAPI_KEY=

# Ticketmaster Discovery — events (the dynamic-characteristics layer). Free dev tier (~5k/day).
# Use the app's *Consumer Key* (Discovery ignores the secret).
# https://developer.ticketmaster.com/  → My Apps → default app → Consumer Key
TICKETMASTER_KEY=

# WSDOT Traveler Information — an example regional traffic provider (Washington State's DOT;
# swap in your own region's feed — most US states publish an equivalent 511 feed — or leave unset), for
# `hn travel traffic`: live travel-time congestion
# deltas + highway alerts (construction/closures). Keyed-FREE — register an email for an AccessCode
# (notify-only, not shared). WSF ferries reuse the same code. https://wsdot.wa.gov/traffic/api/
WSDOT_API_KEY=

# ── finance (hn finance) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Alpaca market data — read-only quotes/bars. Free tier (real-time IEX + 15-min-delayed SIP).
# Generate at https://app.alpaca.markets/ (a paper account is fine; market data is account-agnostic).
ALPACA_API_KEY_ID=
ALPACA_API_SECRET_KEY=

# ── shared ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the tracker corpus repo the toolkit reads/writes. Defaults to ~/projects/corpus if unset.
# Leave commented to use the default (a blank value is treated as unset).
# TRACKER_PATH=

# Weight pack — a portable, swappable scenario bundle (the lanes it provides read from <pack>/<lane>/…).
# Equivalent to the trailing `--pack` flag (`hn finance networth --pack <dir>`); the flag wins per call.
# Point it at a bundled sample to explore the lanes out-of-the-box, e.g.:
#   WEIGHTS_PACK=samples/packs/demo-investor    # finance · the ~$1M fictional household
# Leave commented (blank = unset) to use your own corpus / the packaged defaults.
# WEIGHTS_PACK=
